Jubilee Hospital has had to close its theatres for surgery due to hygiene concerns. PRETORIA - Hammanskraal in northern Gauteng has experienced numerous water issues in the past year and now has reportedly been without water for three weeks. These issues have subsequently affected healthcare in the area. READ: Hammanskraal water 'unfit for consumption', says SAHRC Jubilee Hospital has had to close its theatres for surgery due to hygiene concerns. Committee members have complained that the municipality has not communicated effectively regarding the crisis and have no information on a date for when they will have running water.